n    *   **Final Display:** Must display \\"SIMULATION PASSED\\" or \\"SIMULATION FAILED - x MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME y\\" based on the final error count (`stats1.errors_f`).\\n    *   **First Mismatch Display:** When the first mismatch occurs, it must display inputs, outputs (DUT and Expected), and expected signals at that time.\\n    *   **Error Counting:** The original logic for error counting must be maintained.\\n\\n**Corrections and Enhancements applied to the Golden TB:**\\n*   **Error Reporting Logic:** The original testbench used a `final` block for reporting. This was replaced with an `initial` block that runs after waiting for simulation completion (or a timeout) to ensure all assertions are evaluated. This block strictly implements the required final success/failure messages.\\n*   **First Mismatch Logging:** Logic was added within the `always @(posedge clk, negedge clk)` block to specifically trigger detailed `$display` output when `stats1.errors == 1` (for overall mismatch) and when `stats1.errors_f == 1` (for output mismatch), adhering to the display requirements.\\n*   **Signal Connections:** The TB connects the stimulus generator outputs (`stim1.x3`, `stim1.x2`, `stim1.x1`) to the DUT inputs (`x3_tb`, `x2_tb`, `x1_tb`) and subsequently connects these to the DUT instantiation.\\n*   **Display Formatting:** The detailed display logic for mismatches was implemented to show inputs (in binary and hex), DUT output, and Expected output, fulfilling the requirement for multi-bit signal display (though here all are 1-bit).\\n*   **Syntax Cleanup:** Errors identified in the failed log (like missing quotes, improper assignment syntax) were corrected by ensuring all SystemVerilog constructs are valid, particularly in the reporting `$display` statements.\\n\\n**Advice to avoid syntax error:**\\n1.  **Module Structure:** Ensure every module starts with `module <name>` and ends with `endmodule`.\\n2.  **Signal Declaration:** Use explicit types (`logic` or `reg`) for signals, especially when mixing procedural assignments (`reg`) and continuous assignments (`wire`).\\n3.  **Task Delimiters:** Ensure tasks/functions are correctly delimited (e.g., `endtask`).\\n4.  **Display Strings:** Pay extreme attention to closing all string literals (`"      \n\n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n               \n  